almost linear, convergent distally; cell bm+dm short, ending at level of R 
<number box="[169,177,2014,2028]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" value="1.0">1</number>
. Halter variably blackish, somewhat paler dorsally and on stem; sometimes entirely dirty white. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1312,1428,1999,2024]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Abdomen</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
Black dusted greyish but sternite 
<number box="[527,541,152,176]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" value="1.0">1</number>
with at least proximal 
<number box="[801,836,151,176]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" value="0.5">0.5</number>
whitish, sternite 
<number box="[1030,1044,152,176]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" value="2.0">2</number>
whitish with dark median line and posterolateral marks; all setulae small except posteriorly and laterally on sternite 
<number box="[1078,1095,189,212]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" value="7.0">7</number>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1107,1238,188,213]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Terminalia</emphasis>
. Black with dark setae. Cercus elongate (
<figureCitation box="[419,551,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 68 – 70" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1036,1059]" captionTargetBox="[157,1426,206,1012]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[151,1435,195,1015]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 68 – 70. Male terminalia of Hemerodromia yunnanensis Yang &amp; Ya ng. 68, lateral view of terminalia; 69, dorsal view of cerci; 70, apex of lower narrow process (lower lobe of surstylus?). Abbreviations: cer = cerci, epa = epandrium, hyp = hypandrium, sur = surstylus (upper lobe?)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/289957/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Figs 68, 69</figureCitation>
), extending well beyond apex of epandrium; narrow in lateral view; distinctly setose dorsally. Epandrium bluntly pointed ovoid, with strong setae distally. Hypandrium, with strong setae posteroventrally. Surstylus present, extending beyond tip of epandrium, conspicuously inflated apically where broadly L-shaped with close set minute black setulae in inner face. An elongate apically hook-shaped process (possibly lower lobe of surstylus) emerging just beyond tip of epandrium (
<figureCitation box="[981,1064,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 68 – 70" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1036,1059]" captionTargetBox="[157,1426,206,1012]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[151,1435,195,1015]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 68 – 70. Male terminalia of Hemerodromia yunnanensis Yang &amp; Ya ng. 68, lateral view of terminalia; 69, dorsal view of cerci; 70, apex of lower narrow process (lower lobe of surstylus?). Abbreviations: cer = cerci, epa = epandrium, hyp = hypandrium, sur = surstylus (upper lobe?)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/289957/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
Fig. 
<number box="[1032,1064,368,392]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" value="70.0">70</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1084,1171,367,392]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Female</emphasis>
: Similar to male but F 
<number box="[1426,1436,368,392]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" value="1.0">1</number>
with femoral formula 
<number box="[396,440,404,429]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" value="8.0" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="7.0">
7– 
<date box="[426,440,404,429]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" value="2014-09-16" valueMax="2014-09-17" valueMin="2014-09-16">9</date>
</number>
/ 
<number box="[449,520,404,429]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" value="16.5" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="16.0">16–17</number>
/ 
<number box="[529,600,404,429]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" value="16.0" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="14.0">14–18</number>
+ 
<number box="[616,625,404,429]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[635,663,404,429]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" value="10.0">10</number>
; basal spine of pv row much stronger, at least as long as limb is deep. Abdomen with less conspicuous setae distally but tergite 
<number box="[793,807,440,463]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" value="7.0">7</number>
